- Why not?

303
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:00,160
Because you have to figure
this thing out for yourself.

304
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:03,360
Are you listening to me? Figure it
out, figure it out. Figure out what?

305
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:06,560
- Let it come to you, man.
- I don't have time for this right now.

306
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:10,520
- I'm in the middle of a deal.
- Well, you're working on a new deal now, baby.

307
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,360
What's this?
Open it.

308
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:19,000
What is it,
some kind of a signal?

309
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:24,240
Will you come
whenever I ring it?

310
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:26,240
Now you gotta
get out of the car, Jack.

311
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:31,880
But what do I do? I'm sorry. I
can't spend any more time with you.

312
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,480
- I got some other business I gotta take care of.
- No, y-y-you did this to me.

313
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,640
You can't just leave me like this.

314
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:44,400
Okay. Look, you wanna get some air?
Let's get outside, get some air.

315
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:47,320
We'll walk and I'll explain
everything to you, okay?

316
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,920
- Thanks, man.
- Sure.

317
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:43,880
Excuse me. Do you know
where Merrison Street is?

318
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Jeannie.

319
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:48,720
- I found Jack.
- Oh, there you are, stranger.

320
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,160
Where you been?

321
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,160
You look terrible.
Truth is, I expected you.

322
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:04,680
Kate called and asked
if I knew where you were, so...

323
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:11,240
Oh, I put the Barcalounger in the center
of the room. It's throwing everybody off.

324
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,160
What do you think?

325
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:19,160
It's a great room.
Great room.

326
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:21,000
You and me, buddy,
we know how to live, huh?

327
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,880
Come on.

328
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,720
Come on, Jack.
Come on...

329
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:34,280
Come on, buddy.
Take your seat.

330
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:43,640
Are you okay?

331
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:47,400
I mean, you take off Christmas morning and
you don't tell anyone where you're going.

332
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:54,560
- We're friends?
- Talk to me.

333
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,320
I'm having kind of a bad day.

334
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:03,800
You know, I read somewhere that the
suicide rate doubles during the holiday.

335
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:06,600
What am I saying that for?
You don't wanna hear that. Come on.

336
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:11,240
Is it...
Is it trouble at work?

337
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:14,400
I... I don't think so.

338
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,360
Well, it's not Kate, is it?

339
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,720
You see, huh? It's like we're
inside each other's heads.

340
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,760
Kate's my wife.

341
00:27:25,840 --> 00:27:29,960
Just keep saying it over and over again,
Jack, like a mantra. Keep saying it.

342
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:39,040
Look, you know,
you fit the profile exactly...

343
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:43,320
in your 30s, house, kids,
financial responsibilities.

344
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:46,600
You start thinking this
isn't the life I dreamt about.

345
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:49,320
Where's the romance,
you know?

346
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,760
Where's the joie de vivre?

347
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:57,000
Suddenly every lingerie ad
in the Newark Star-Ledger...

348
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:59,560
represents a life
that you can't have.

349
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:04,680
It's just two kids, right?

350
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,040
Come on. Come on.

351
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:13,680
All right, sometimes it feels like you
gave up the whole world. I know that.

352
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:17,000
But look what you got.
Look at that: four bedrooms,

353
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:20,040
two-and-a-half baths,
a partially finished basement.

354
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:23,000
And good kids.
Look. You know what?

355
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:25,360
You probably don't wanna
hear this right now.

356
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:29,080
But remember last summer when I almost had
that thing with Arnie, Jr. 's speech therapist?

357
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,960
You remember what
you said to me?

358
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:35,720
You said, "Don't screw up
the best thing in your life...

359
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:38,560
just because you're a little
unsure about who you are."

360
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,520
Okay?

361
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:51,560
Go get 'em, tiger.

362
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:25,360
Could you hold on a second?

363
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:37,240
Um, never mind because...
because he just walked in.

364
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:39,440
Thank you. Thank you.

365
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:46,040
Do you... have any idea
what you put us through today?

366
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,520
You walk out of here
at 7:30 in the morning.

367
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:53,320
You don't tell me where you're
going, or even that you're going.

368
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,720
And I don't see you
till hours later?

369
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:59,080
I called all of our friends. I had
the state troopers looking for you.

370
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:02,120
I was on the phone with the
hospital, for God's sakes.

371
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:06,800
What kind of man leaves his family on Christmas
morning without a word about where he's going?

372
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:10,000
- What kind of a man does that, Jack?
- I don't know.

373
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:13,160
Could you... Could you please
stop yelling at me?

374
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:20,600
- Where were you?
- I was in the city.

375
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:23,880
The city?
New York City?

376
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,120
- Yeah.
- Why?

377
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:33,280
- Because that's where I live.
- Don't start, Jack. Don't.

378
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:35,680
Look, you don't understand.

379
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:38,840
I... I... I woke up
this morning here.

380
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:43,560
And this is very strange
because...

381
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,480
this isn't my house.

382
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:48,480
And those aren't my kids.
I'm not Dad.

383
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:51,880
I- I-I'm not a dad.
You're not my wife.

384
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:54,280
You know what, Jack.
It's not funny this time...

385
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:56,200
because I am really mad.

386
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,680
I mean, really mad.
I mean it.

387
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,080
I don't even...

388
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:06,120
What...

389
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:08,280
What's that?

390
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:15,080
I like it.
Thanks, Dad.

391
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,560
That's mine. Hey,
I need that back.

392
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,800
She took my bell.

393
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,280
You missed the whole thing...

394
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:26,000
the pancakes and the presents.

395
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:29,440
You spent six hours putting
that bike together for Annie,

396
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:32,960
and then you didn't even get to see
the look on her face when she opened it.

397
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:37,160
You missed Christmas, Jack.

398
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,640
I'm sorry.

399
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:47,600
You know, we don't even
have enough time for this.

400
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:50,800
And at least you're okay.
I'm okay, we're okay.

401
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:54,920
But you've gotta get dressed for the
Thompson party. And you are not wearing that.

402
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,120
I don't care how hilarious
you think it is.

403
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:59,600
Party? No, I'm not
going to a party.

404
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:02,880
You look forward to this party all
year. What is it with you today?

405
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:06,000
Believe me, Kate. I really don't
think that going to a party...

406
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:08,280
is the right move for me
at the present time.

407
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:12,360
Okay, fine. You know what? Then
you just do whatever you wanna do.

408
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:16,280
- What are you doing?
- Telling my mother she doesn't
have to stay with the kids.

409
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:19,000
- Why not?
- Because you'll be here.

410
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:25,600
I'll be ready in ten minutes.

411
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:36,800
This is... This is
just subpar.

412
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:02,240
# Oh, the weather outside
is frightful #

413
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:04,840
Lance, here you go.

414
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:07,920
Excuse me.

415
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:12,880
# Let it snow, let it snow
Let it snow #

416
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:15,880
# It doesn't show
signs of stopping ##

417
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,960
- Kate. Jack.
- Evelyn.

418
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:20,920
Come in. Hey, everybody,
Kate and Jack are here.

419
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,920
- Hey!
- Jeannie.

420
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:25,040
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

421
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:27,120
Jack, Merry Christmas.

422
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:32,080
Whoops.
Here.

423
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:35,040
- So, like the dress?
- Oh, it's lovely.

424
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:38,560
I thought I saw you notice
it at the kids' recital.

425
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:40,800
It's lovely.
It's lovely.

426
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:52,760
There he is.

427
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:55,920
- Hey, Jack. Happy holidays, man.
- Yeah.

428
00:33:57,280 --> 00:33:59,400
Jack, come on over.

429
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:05,640
Hey, Jack.
Cheers, baby.

430
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:08,680
- You guys see Van Horn last night?
- Thirty-two points.

431
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:12,040
- That kid's gonna take the Nets to the championship.
- The Nets? Are you kidding?

432
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,960
They suck.

433
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:19,640
But they're due.
They're certainly due.

434
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:22,440
So, tomorrow's
the big day, Jackie.

435
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:25,200
Okay. Why?

436
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:27,760
My triple bypass.

437
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:30,320
I'm going under the knife
tomorrow. I told you that, right?

438
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,240
- Triple bypass.
- Yeah.

439
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:34,680
You really think you should
be eating all that?

440
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,600
Figure I'm going in
for a cleaning tomorrow.

441
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:38,760
Might as well load up on the
fried stuff tonight, right?

442
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:41,240
That's good thinking, Bill.
Have another drink.

443
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:45,480
Some fried pork, mashed potatoes.
He'll be dead by morning.

444
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:48,440
- How 'bout a cigar, Jack?
- Oh, no, thank you. I'm cutting down.

445
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:51,240
- Come on. They're American made, not Cuban.
- Oh, really?

446
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:52,840
Come on.

447
00:34:55,240 --> 00:34:57,320
- Very nice.
- I thought you'd like 'em.

448
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,440
Superb.

449
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,080
- How 'bout you, Arnie?
- I'm all right. Thanks.

450
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:10,120
- Finger food?
- No, thank you. I'm fine.

451
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,760
