953
01:15:21,200 --> 01:15:23,360
I don't have it all figured out.

954
01:15:23,440 --> 01:15:25,120
Me neither.

955
01:15:25,200 --> 01:15:27,320
But you always seem so certain.

956
01:15:27,400 --> 01:15:29,880
Do you think there aren't
mornings when I wake up...

957
01:15:30,000 --> 01:15:32,440
and wonder, "What the hell
am I doing in New Jersey?"

958
01:15:32,520 --> 01:15:34,240
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

959
01:15:34,360 --> 01:15:37,760
- Yeah.
- My office is a dump.

960
01:15:37,880 --> 01:15:40,920
I answer my own phone,
and you seen my paycheck.

961
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:44,240
Your paycheck is a disgrace
to paychecks.

962
01:15:45,440 --> 01:15:47,880
Can you imagine a life...

963
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:50,360
where everything was just easy?

964
01:15:50,440 --> 01:15:54,680
You know, where you ask for things,
and people just bring them to you?

965
01:15:54,760 --> 01:15:56,400
It's wonderful.

966
01:16:04,160 --> 01:16:06,000
I think about it too.

967
01:16:06,120 --> 01:16:08,320
I do.

968
01:16:08,440 --> 01:16:12,200
I wonder about what kind of life I
would have had if I hadn't married you.

969
01:16:12,360 --> 01:16:13,840
And?

970
01:16:15,760 --> 01:16:19,880
Then I realize I've just erased all the
things in my life that I'm sure about.

971
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:22,480
You and the kids.

972
01:16:22,640 --> 01:16:24,400
Good things.

973
01:16:24,560 --> 01:16:26,160
Yeah.

974
01:16:28,440 --> 01:16:30,360
What are you sure about?

975
01:16:31,880 --> 01:16:33,720
I'm sure that right now,

976
01:16:33,800 --> 01:16:36,440
there's nowhere else I'd
rather be than here with you.

977
01:16:49,920 --> 01:16:51,920
Oh.

978
01:16:52,000 --> 01:16:53,840
Oh, Jack.

979
01:16:58,920 --> 01:17:01,040
You like it?

980
01:17:08,240 --> 01:17:10,920
This is beautiful.

981
01:17:13,960 --> 01:17:16,760
You know champagne
makes me do crazy things.

982
01:17:16,840 --> 01:17:19,840
I'll just fill yours
up to the top.

983
01:17:23,440 --> 01:17:26,560
I don't know how you did it,
Hoss, but you pulled it off.

984
01:17:26,680 --> 01:17:29,520
- I'm out of the doghouse?
- Way out.

985
01:17:31,600 --> 01:17:34,280
Happy anniversary, sweetheart.

986
01:17:37,960 --> 01:17:40,720
You may even get lucky
tonight, Jack.

987
01:17:47,840 --> 01:17:50,760
You're so beautiful.

988
01:17:50,840 --> 01:17:53,640
I already told you
you were gonna get lucky.

989
01:17:56,520 --> 01:17:59,000
My God.

990
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:01,240
All this time,

991
01:18:01,320 --> 01:18:04,200
I never stopped loving you.

992
01:18:09,720 --> 01:18:12,040
That's all I wanted to hear.

993
01:18:41,640 --> 01:18:44,920
I'm gonna wear the usual today.

994
01:18:45,000 --> 01:18:46,840
What are you thinking?

995
01:18:46,960 --> 01:18:50,720
You want to come to work
with Dad, help me sell tires?

996
01:18:50,800 --> 01:18:53,320
It's fun.
I'm pretty good at it.

997
01:18:53,440 --> 01:18:56,920
Who's this? Who's that?
Who is that?

998
01:18:57,040 --> 01:18:59,400
Who's on that tie?

999
01:18:59,520 --> 01:19:01,080
That's Grandpa.

1000
01:19:01,200 --> 01:19:02,840
Yes.

1001
01:19:05,040 --> 01:19:06,880
Jack!

1002
01:19:12,280 --> 01:19:14,080
Mmm.

1003
01:19:17,200 --> 01:19:19,600
Have a great day.

1004
01:19:25,000 --> 01:19:28,240
For the money, this is hands
down the best radial we carry.

1005
01:19:28,320 --> 01:19:30,680
Okay.
I guess I'll take 'em.

1006
01:19:30,800 --> 01:19:32,640
You won't regret it.
Tommy.

1007
01:19:32,720 --> 01:19:35,960
Would you set Mr. Collin up with four
B.F. Goodrich G-Force T.A.'s?

1008
01:19:36,040 --> 01:19:40,800
Give him ten percent off for
having the best costume. Thank you.

1009
01:19:40,880 --> 01:19:43,120
You bet. Right this way, sir. Follow me.

1010
01:19:43,240 --> 01:19:45,040
Tell me, does the tire
smell good?

1011
01:19:47,720 --> 01:19:50,080
Remember our
Valentine's Day special:

1012
01:19:50,200 --> 01:19:52,760
balance and alignment for free!

1013
01:19:57,800 --> 01:20:01,360
How are you doing today?
It just blew out on me.

1014
01:20:01,440 --> 01:20:03,760
Do you have a tire like that?

1015
01:20:05,760 --> 01:20:08,040
I seem to have
some sort of a blowout here.

1016
01:20:08,160 --> 01:20:10,800
- Why don't you let me take this one, Kenny?
- Okay, chief.

1017
01:20:10,880 --> 01:20:13,480
Peter Lassiter.

1018
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:15,560
- Do I know you?
- Not exactly.

1019
01:20:15,680 --> 01:20:19,160
I've seen you on CNBC.
You look taller in real life.

1020
01:20:21,120 --> 01:20:24,200
Truth is, Mintz was so busy
timing his wife's breathing,

1021
01:20:24,360 --> 01:20:27,960
he didn't realize that Med Tech needed
Global more than the other way around.

1022
01:20:28,080 --> 01:20:30,680
Ten days, two weeks tops, they would
have approached you with an offer.

1023
01:20:30,800 --> 01:20:35,120
I'm willing to bet anything it
would have been 130 billion, not 122.

1024
01:20:35,240 --> 01:20:38,400
The trouble is, Peter, you had
a pussycat running the show.

1025
01:20:38,520 --> 01:20:40,760
What you needed was a Doberman.

1026
01:20:42,960 --> 01:20:45,680
I'm impressed.
I really am.

1027
01:20:47,080 --> 01:20:48,920
Now, about my car.

1028
01:20:51,040 --> 01:20:53,760
Sure. We're gonna have to
special order that tire,

1029
01:20:53,880 --> 01:20:56,320
so it'll be ready
in a couple of days.

1030
01:20:56,440 --> 01:21:01,520
All right.
This is my office address.

1031
01:21:05,600 --> 01:21:08,160
Why don't you drop off
the car yourself?

1032
01:21:37,040 --> 01:21:40,160
We're really more of a boutique
operation, as you can see.

1033
01:21:40,280 --> 01:21:43,560
But you're not interested in
boutique dollars. I get it.

1034
01:21:43,640 --> 01:21:46,040
He's expecting you,
Mr. Lassiter.

1035
01:21:47,560 --> 01:21:49,880
Alan, this is Jack Campbell,

1036
01:21:49,960 --> 01:21:52,080
the one I was telling you about.

1037
01:21:52,200 --> 01:21:54,760
- Of course. Jack. Hi.
- Mr. Mintz.

1038
01:21:54,840 --> 01:21:59,120
No, just call me Alan. We like to
cultivate a very casual atmosphere here.

1039
01:22:00,560 --> 01:22:03,440
- I can see that.
- What can I tell you? Do you have kids?

1040
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:07,480
Uh, actually, yes.
Two of them. Good ones.

1041
01:22:07,560 --> 01:22:10,360
Great, great.
Why don't you have a seat?

1042
01:22:10,440 --> 01:22:14,360
Peter mentioned to me that
you're an avid CNBC watcher.

1043
01:22:14,440 --> 01:22:19,160
But he didn't say whether you had
any actual Wall Street experience.

1044
01:22:21,080 --> 01:22:24,560
Um, I was a sales associate
at E.F. Hutton.

1045
01:22:24,680 --> 01:22:26,880
A broker, really?

1046
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:29,360
And now you're in
the tire business?

1047
01:22:29,480 --> 01:22:31,520
That's right.
And auto supply.

1048
01:22:31,720 --> 01:22:33,640
In the retail end, I understand.

1049
01:22:33,760 --> 01:22:36,800
We get about 60 percent of our
business from automotive service.

1050
01:22:38,400 --> 01:22:41,200
And do you mind me asking what kind
of sales you did in the last year?

1051
01:22:41,320 --> 01:22:45,080
Just ball park. We did
1.7 million in total revenue.

1052
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:47,200
1.7. That's great.

1053
01:22:47,360 --> 01:22:49,400
And what do you project
for this year?

1054
01:22:49,480 --> 01:22:51,600
I think we're gonna have
a banner year.

1055
01:22:51,720 --> 01:22:54,160
Sales are up almost 20 percent
in the first quarter,

1056
01:22:54,280 --> 01:22:56,520
and we just landed a major
trucking company account.

1057
01:22:56,600 --> 01:22:59,840
You did? That's great. So that puts
you just a tad over two million?

1058
01:22:59,920 --> 01:23:03,400
That's right. And that would
make us number one in our market.

1059
01:23:03,520 --> 01:23:05,680
Excuse me. I'm gonna get
a glass of water.

1060
01:23:15,840 --> 01:23:20,200
Look, I know our paltry
little $2 million in sales...

1061
01:23:20,280 --> 01:23:23,080
is about what you spend a year
on office supplies.

1062
01:23:23,160 --> 01:23:25,960
And some regional trucking company
account is nothing compared...

1063
01:23:26,040 --> 01:23:28,960
- to a multi-billion-dollar merger.
- No, no, no.

1064
01:23:29,040 --> 01:23:32,080
- I'm not trying to knock the tire business.
- It's okay, Alan. I get it.

1065
01:23:32,160 --> 01:23:35,520
I'm in your shoes, I'm thinking
the same thing, but here's the deal.

1066
01:23:35,640 --> 01:23:38,360
Business is business.
Wall Street, Main Street.

1067
01:23:38,440 --> 01:23:40,800
It's all a bunch of people
getting up in the morning,

1068
01:23:40,880 --> 01:23:43,440
trying to figure out how they're
going to send their kids to college.

1069
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:47,040
It's just people,
and I know people.

1070
01:23:47,160 --> 01:23:49,920
- Oh, I'm sure you do.
- Take you, for instance, Alan.

1071
01:23:50,000 --> 01:23:52,840
You have a certain energy about
you, an active kind of energy.

1072
01:23:52,960 --> 01:23:55,680
I wouldn't be surprised if you
drank about 16 Diet Cokes a day.

1073
01:23:55,760 --> 01:24:00,640
You're an excellent father, but you feel
guilty about the time you spend away from home.

1074
01:24:00,720 --> 01:24:03,240
You drink bourbon, but you
offer your clients Scotch.

1075
01:24:03,360 --> 01:24:06,920
And your wife
decorated this office.

1076
01:24:07,040 --> 01:24:09,440
He certainly seems
to have your number.

1077
01:24:09,520 --> 01:24:11,400
You're a little tougher,
Peter.

1078
01:24:11,480 --> 01:24:13,560
For one thing,
you like expensive things.

1079
01:24:13,640 --> 01:24:16,880
That's easy.
You've seen my car.

1080
01:24:18,240 --> 01:24:20,320
You smoke Hoyo de Monterreys.

1081
01:24:20,400 --> 01:24:22,440
You're a Scotch man, single malt,

1082
01:24:22,520 --> 01:24:25,720
not because it's trendy but because
you've been doing it for 40 years...

1083
01:24:25,800 --> 01:24:28,280
and you like to stay
with what works.

1084
01:24:28,400 --> 01:24:31,480
You have two great loves
in your life: your horses...

1085
01:24:31,600 --> 01:24:33,640
and this company.

1086
01:24:33,800 --> 01:24:38,160
And you're a man who prides himself
in finding talent in unusual places.

1087
01:24:39,720 --> 01:24:42,640
- How would you know that?
- Because I'm here.

1088
01:24:42,760 --> 01:24:45,320
I'm prepared to do whatever
it takes to get this job.

1089
01:24:45,400 --> 01:24:47,200
I'll start wherever
I have to start.

1090
01:24:47,280 --> 01:24:49,120
I'll park cars if I have to.

1091
01:24:49,200 --> 01:24:52,600
The biggest part of judging character
is knowing yourself, and I know this:

1092
01:24:52,720 --> 01:24:56,120
I can do this job.
I can.

1093
01:24:56,240 --> 01:24:59,360
Give me a chance, Peter.
I won't let you down.

1094
01:25:04,800 --> 01:25:08,160
Alan, why don't you
show Jack around?

1095
01:25:08,280 --> 01:25:11,680
This is our war room. We did seven
major deals in here last year,

1096
01:25:11,840 --> 01:25:13,920
three of them... hostile.

1097
01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:16,640
- Seven?
- Yeah. You get a kind of a feeling from...

1098
01:25:16,800 --> 01:25:19,560
Can we cut the shit here for a minute?
Where did you get that information?

1099
01:25:19,680 --> 01:25:22,240
Did you go through his wallet?
Did you surf some Net?

1100
01:25:22,320 --> 01:25:25,080
It doesn't really matter because that
circus act you pulled back there...

1101
01:25:25,160 --> 01:25:27,520
may have dazzled Lassiter, but
it doesn't cut any shit with me.

1102
01:25:27,600 --> 01:25:29,840
Even if you get this job,
which I highly doubt,

1103
01:25:29,920 --> 01:25:31,760
let me just give you
a word of warning.

1104
01:25:31,840 --> 01:25:35,080
Peter Lassiter gets tired of his
pet projects very, very quickly.

1105
01:25:35,200 --> 01:25:38,960
I've got that big office because I prove
myself to him year after year after year.

1106
01:25:39,040 --> 01:25:41,440
Nobody is gonna come in here
and turn the old man's head,

1107
01:25:41,600 --> 01:25:44,360
especially not some tire
salesman from New Jersey.

1108
01:25:44,480 --> 01:25:46,880
So if you're cautious
and you're quiet,

1109
01:25:47,040 --> 01:25:49,320
you watch yourself,
stay away from Lassiter,

1110
01:25:49,440 --> 01:25:52,440
maybe I'll think about keeping you
on here after he gets bored with you.

1111
01:25:52,560 --> 01:25:54,360
Do we understand each other?

1112
01:25:55,880 --> 01:25:58,080
Alan!

1113
01:25:58,200 --> 01:26:00,000
God, you really are different.

1114
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:02,640
- Excuse me?
- I mean, wow!

1115
01:26:02,760 --> 01:26:06,360
I'm impressed. I'm impressed.
Good for you.

1116
01:26:08,560 --> 01:26:10,560
Are we understanding
each other?

1117
01:26:10,640 --> 01:26:12,520
Yes, Alan, I understand you.

1118
01:26:12,600 --> 01:26:15,200
- Okay then.
- Good.

1119
01:26:15,360 --> 01:26:18,440
- Good.
- Okay. Okay.

1120
01:26:18,560 --> 01:26:20,360
Alan!

1121
01:26:27,680 --> 01:26:30,520
Keep your eyes closed.
Hold on.

1122
01:26:34,080 --> 01:26:36,360
Go ahead.
Open your eyes.

1123
01:26:36,440 --> 01:26:38,280
Welcome to Xanadu.

1124
01:26:41,080 --> 01:26:43,840
It's pretty incredible,
isn't it?

1125
01:26:43,920 --> 01:26:46,680
It's like a museum.

1126
01:26:50,920 --> 01:26:52,760
Look around.

1127
01:27:00,400 --> 01:27:02,200
So what's the big surprise?

1128
01:27:02,320 --> 01:27:04,720
You didn't rent this
for the weekend, did you?

1129
01:27:04,800 --> 01:27:07,640
Think... bigger.

1130
01:27:07,720 --> 01:27:09,720
For the week?

1131
01:27:09,840 --> 01:27:12,480
This place is a perk, Kate.

1132
01:27:14,320 --> 01:27:17,120
A perk?

1133
01:27:17,240 --> 01:27:18,960
For what?

1134
01:27:19,080 --> 01:27:21,880
A company called P.K. Lassiter
Investment House...

1135
01:27:21,960 --> 01:27:25,080
uses it to attract
new executives.

1136
01:27:25,160 --> 01:27:27,320
I'm going into arbitrage, honey.

1137
01:27:27,440 --> 01:27:29,720
It turns out
I have a knack for it.

1138
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:33,680
Jack, what are you
talking about?

1139
01:27:33,800 --> 01:27:37,360
I'll be making twice what I
make now, plus a hefty bonus.

1140
01:27:37,440 --> 01:27:40,080
That's just to start. And we
can live in this apartment...

1141
01:27:40,160 --> 01:27:41,880
practically rent free...

1142
01:27:41,960 --> 01:27:44,240
until we find a place of our own.

1143
01:27:44,360 --> 01:27:47,280
Are you out of your mind?

1144
01:27:47,400 --> 01:27:49,240
I don't think so.

1145
01:27:49,360 --> 01:27:52,240
This is gonna be a better life for all of us.
We can put Annie and Josh into private schools.

1146
01:27:52,360 --> 01:27:54,360
Annie goes to
a great school, Jack.

1147
01:27:54,520 --> 01:27:57,000
I'm talking about the best
schools in the country here.

1148
01:27:57,120 --> 01:28:00,800
What could you possibly be
thinking about? What about my job?

1149
01:28:00,880 --> 01:28:04,080
Well, this is New York City. It's like
the needy people capital of the world.

1150
01:28:04,160 --> 01:28:08,240
Your Jersey clients aren't a tenth as
pathetic as the ones you could find here.

1151
01:28:08,320 --> 01:28:11,840
I can't even believe you're talking
about moving back into the city.

1152
01:28:11,920 --> 01:28:15,440
I thought the reason we left was because
we didn't want to raise the kids here.

1153
01:28:15,560 --> 01:28:18,680
No. No. This is the
center of the universe.

1154
01:28:18,760 --> 01:28:21,400
If I were living in Roman times,
I would live in Rome. Where else?

1155
01:28:21,520 --> 01:28:24,160
"Today America is the Roman
empire. New York is Rome itself."

1156
01:28:24,320 --> 01:28:26,120
- John Lennon.
- Jack!

1157
01:28:26,240 --> 01:28:29,480
Okay, you know something? I'm
detecting, like, a funky tension here.

1158
01:28:29,600 --> 01:28:33,360
This was supposed to be a happy day,
so guess what? I don't need this.

1159
01:28:33,440 --> 01:28:35,880
We don't have to live here.
Forget it.

1160
01:28:36,040 --> 01:28:38,720
- I'll commute. I'll drive to work.
- God!

1161
01:28:38,800 --> 01:28:42,880
In traffic, it's over an hour each
way. That's three hours every day.

1162
01:28:42,960 --> 01:28:46,840
- When are you ever going to see the kids?
- Kate.

1163
01:28:46,960 --> 01:28:48,960
You're not understanding me.

1164
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:52,840
I'm talking about a
perfect life, a great life.

1165
01:28:52,920 --> 01:28:55,320
Everything we pictured when we
were young. The whole package.

1166
01:28:55,480 --> 01:28:58,280
You said so yourself.
Life has thrown us a few surprises,

1167
01:28:58,400 --> 01:29:00,240
so we made sacrifices.
Well, guess what?

1168
01:29:00,400 --> 01:29:03,520
Now I can finally get us back
on track. I can do that, Kate.

1169
01:29:03,600 --> 01:29:07,600
I want to do that.
I need to do that as a man!

1170
01:29:07,680 --> 01:29:09,680
For all of us.

1171
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:14,800
Please just think about this
for one second.

1172
01:29:14,920 --> 01:29:17,600
No more lousy restaurants.

1173
01:29:17,720 --> 01:29:19,760
No more clipping coupons.

1174
01:29:19,840 --> 01:29:21,680
No more shoveling snow.

1175
01:29:21,760 --> 01:29:23,840
Then get a goddamn
snowblower, Jack!

1176
01:29:23,920 --> 01:29:27,800
Don't go get a new career
without even telling me about it!

1177
01:29:29,280 --> 01:29:31,640
And don't... don't take Annie
out of a school she loves.

1178
01:29:31,760 --> 01:29:36,120
Don't move us out of a house
we've become a family in.

1179
01:29:38,760 --> 01:29:41,200
You're... You're...

1180
01:29:41,280 --> 01:29:45,080
Don't you see? I'm talking
about us finally having a life...

1181
01:29:45,160 --> 01:29:47,000
that other people envy.

1182
01:29:47,080 --> 01:29:48,920
Oh, Jack.

1183
01:29:50,440 --> 01:29:53,040
They already do envy us.

1184
01:30:50,960 --> 01:30:53,000
From London to New York.

1185
01:30:55,480 --> 01:30:57,320
I came back.

1186
01:31:04,440 --> 01:31:08,080
When you got on that plane,
I was sure it was over.

1187
01:31:10,640 --> 01:31:14,880
I left the airport afraid
I'd never see you again.

1188
01:31:14,960 --> 01:31:17,760
And then you showed up
the very next day.

1189
01:31:20,840 --> 01:31:23,200
That was a good surprise.

1190
01:31:26,560 --> 01:31:30,400
You know, I think about
the decision you made.

1191
01:31:35,720 --> 01:31:38,400
Maybe I was being naive,
but I believed...

1192
01:31:38,560 --> 01:31:42,800
that we would grow old together
in this house,

1193
01:31:42,920 --> 01:31:46,920
that we'd spend holidays
here and...

1194
01:31:49,400 --> 01:31:52,800
have our grandchildren
come visit us here.

1195
01:31:54,280 --> 01:31:58,320
I had this image of us
all gray and wrinkly,

1196
01:31:59,800 --> 01:32:02,440
and me...
working in the garden,

1197
01:32:02,560 --> 01:32:05,280
and you repainting the deck.

1198
01:32:15,880 --> 01:32:19,000
But things change.

1199
01:32:23,120 --> 01:32:25,360
If you need this, Jack,

1200
01:32:25,480 --> 01:32:27,520
if you really need this,

1201
01:32:27,640 --> 01:32:30,000
I will take these kids
from a life they love,

1202
01:32:30,080 --> 01:32:33,040
and I'll take myself from the only
home we've ever shared together...

1203
01:32:33,120 --> 01:32:36,880
and I'll move wherever
you need to go.

1204
01:32:36,960 --> 01:32:39,320
I'll do that
because I love you.

1205
01:32:41,760 --> 01:32:43,800
I love you,

1206
01:32:44,000 --> 01:32:47,640
and that's more important to me
than our address.

1207
01:32:50,200 --> 01:32:52,480
I choose us.

1208
01:33:29,680 --> 01:33:32,160
Oh. I'm gonna chase you.

1209
01:33:32,240 --> 01:33:35,320
You can't catch me.
No, you can't. You can't.

1210
01:33:35,400 --> 01:33:38,520
Oh!

1211
01:33:40,560 --> 01:33:43,200
Whoa! Oh. Whoops!

1212
01:33:43,360 --> 01:33:45,640
I fell down.

1213
01:33:49,320 --> 01:33:52,000
I knew you'd come back.

1214
01:33:57,080 --> 01:33:59,040
Oh, Annie.

1215
01:33:59,200 --> 01:34:00,960
I love you.

1216
01:34:22,760 --> 01:34:26,240
- What are you doing?
- Ringing my bell.

1217
01:34:35,360 --> 01:34:39,120
4.99? It's just salt, for God sakes.

1218
01:34:39,240 --> 01:34:41,240
Ninety-nine cents, darling.

1219
01:34:42,400 --> 01:34:44,680
Out of ten.

1220
01:34:44,760 --> 01:34:48,200
- You!
- Jack!

1221
01:34:48,320 --> 01:34:50,440
What's up?
How you feeling, baby?

1222
01:34:50,560 --> 01:34:53,720
Why are you here?

1223
01:34:55,520 --> 01:34:59,360
Here's your change, darling.
Five, six, seven, eight,

1224
01:34:59,440 --> 01:35:01,760
nine, oh-one.

1225
01:35:01,880 --> 01:35:04,320
Is that rock salt?

1226
01:35:04,400 --> 01:35:07,960
Look at you, man. Went and got
all domestic and everything.

1227
01:35:08,080 --> 01:35:10,080
You really figured
some things out, huh?

1228
01:35:10,200 --> 01:35:12,320
You're not
sending me back.

1229
01:35:13,840 --> 01:35:16,960
- Everything okay?
- Yeah.

1230
01:35:17,080 --> 01:35:19,000
Hey, did you hear me?

1231
01:35:19,120 --> 01:35:21,800
- Wait a second.
- I'm talking to you.

1232
01:35:21,920 --> 01:35:24,080
You see that?

1233
01:35:24,200 --> 01:35:27,680
Character. And for what, for nine
bucks? That's just so disappointing.

1234
01:35:27,760 --> 01:35:30,280
I'm not going back.
You understand me?

1235
01:35:30,360 --> 01:35:32,320
- Okay, relax, Jack.
- You can't do this.

1236
01:35:32,400 --> 01:35:35,160
You can't keep coming in and out of
people's lives, messing things up.

1237
01:35:35,240 --> 01:35:37,080
It's not right.

1238
01:35:37,160 --> 01:35:41,040
A glimpse, by definition,
is an impermanent thing, Jack.

1239
01:35:52,480 --> 01:35:55,320
I've got kids.
I'm going home.

1240
01:36:52,400 --> 01:36:54,320
Is it morning yet?

1241
01:36:54,480 --> 01:36:56,360
No, honey.

1242
01:36:56,440 --> 01:36:58,280
Go back to sleep.

1243
01:37:03,960 --> 01:37:05,800
Take care, Annie.

1244
01:37:08,120 --> 01:37:10,720
I'm going back to the mother ship.

1245
01:37:18,280 --> 01:37:20,120
Hey.

1246
01:37:20,200 --> 01:37:22,040
Hey.

1247
01:37:27,560 --> 01:37:31,760
These past few weeks,
I know I've done some...

1248
01:37:31,880 --> 01:37:34,160
some unusual things.

1249
01:37:35,760 --> 01:37:37,960
It's been interesting,
that's for sure.

1250
01:37:40,280 --> 01:37:42,880
I've done some good things,
too, though, haven't I?

1251
01:37:44,560 --> 01:37:48,080
You've been Jack Campbell,
and that's always a good thing.

1252
01:37:53,400 --> 01:37:56,800
I need you to remember me, Kate.

1253
01:37:56,920 --> 01:37:59,080
How I am right now...

1254
01:37:59,240 --> 01:38:01,800
at this very moment.

1255
01:38:01,920 --> 01:38:05,840
I need you to put that image
in your heart and keep it there.

1256
01:38:05,960 --> 01:38:08,920
Keep it with you
no matter what happens.

1257
01:38:10,760 --> 01:38:14,600
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. Yeah.

1258
01:38:14,680 --> 01:38:17,000
Please just promise me.

1259
01:38:17,120 --> 01:38:20,400
You have to promise me, because if you
don't, then it's like it never happened,

1260
01:38:20,520 --> 01:38:22,520
and I don't think
I can live with that.

1261
01:38:23,840 --> 01:38:25,640
I promise.

1262
01:38:28,440 --> 01:38:30,280
Promise me again.

1263
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:35,840
- I promise.
- Okay.

1264
01:38:35,960 --> 01:38:37,760
Now come to bed.

1265
01:38:40,760 --> 01:38:42,560
Soon.

1266
01:40:32,080 --> 01:40:33,920
Yeah.

1267
01:40:36,240 --> 01:40:38,360
What time is it?

1268
01:40:38,480 --> 01:40:41,000
Okay. Yeah.

1269
01:41:09,560 --> 01:41:12,600
- Waiting for me by the door, huh?
- Paula.

1270
01:41:12,720 --> 01:41:15,080
Wow.

1271
01:41:15,200 --> 01:41:17,440
Merry Christmas.

1272
01:41:17,520 --> 01:41:20,360
Christmas?
It's not Christmas.

1273
01:41:20,440 --> 01:41:22,840
It's whatever you
want it to be, Jack.

1274
01:41:22,920 --> 01:41:24,920
It's not Christmas.

1275
01:41:25,040 --> 01:41:27,520
Jack. Jack?

1276
01:42:11,280 --> 01:42:13,720
Can I help you?

1277
01:42:13,880 --> 01:42:16,280
Is Kate here?

1278
01:42:16,400 --> 01:42:18,320
- Does Kate live here?
- Kate? No.

1279
01:42:18,400 --> 01:42:20,800
There's nobody named Kate here.

1280
01:42:22,840 --> 01:42:24,640
Of course not.

1281
01:42:26,040 --> 01:42:28,000
You okay?

1282
01:42:29,680 --> 01:42:31,480
No.

1283
01:42:43,440 --> 01:42:46,640
Hello.

1284
01:42:46,760 --> 01:42:49,600
Santa Claus, where are you?
Everybody's here.

1285
01:42:49,720 --> 01:42:53,040
- Adelle?
- You're a half an hour late.

1286
01:42:53,200 --> 01:42:55,520
The emergency strategy session?
Trip to Aspen?

1287
01:42:55,600 --> 01:42:57,440
Is this ringing any bells?

1288
01:42:57,520 --> 01:43:00,440
Everybody is panicked
here, Jack.

1289
01:43:02,440 --> 01:43:04,840
Jack?

1290
01:43:04,920 --> 01:43:07,400
I'll be there in 20 minutes.

1291
01:43:07,520 --> 01:43:11,600
No, I'm not gonna go talk to them until
I have something to talk to them about.

1292
01:43:11,680 --> 01:43:14,800
Steve, I don't care if it's
Christmas day. We're in a crisis here.

1293
01:43:14,960 --> 01:43:17,400
Wait a minute. Jack just walked
in. I'll call you back. Jack.

1294
01:43:17,560 --> 01:43:19,880
Thank God that you're...

1295
01:43:19,960 --> 01:43:22,800
- You're here. Are you all right?
- What's going on here?

1296
01:43:22,920 --> 01:43:25,920
What's...
Well, it's not good.

1297
01:43:26,000 --> 01:43:29,800
Bob Thomas has been talking to a European drug
company, Jack, and we don't know which one.

1298
01:43:29,920 --> 01:43:34,280
They're gonna let Bob buy a minority stake,
and let him keep running the entire company.

1299
01:43:34,400 --> 01:43:38,160
Global knows. I don't know how they know,
but they know and they're up in arms.

1300
01:43:38,320 --> 01:43:41,600
They think that somehow we should
have been prepared for this. Prepared!

1301
01:43:41,680 --> 01:43:44,160
Oh, God, we're in trouble.

1302
01:43:44,240 --> 01:43:47,360
You know something, Alan?

1303
01:43:47,440 --> 01:43:51,720
Somewhere inside of you, there's
a much more assertive person.

1304
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:55,480
Is this another one of those
Sun Tzu Art of War tricks?

1305
01:43:56,840 --> 01:43:58,640
No.

1306
01:43:58,800 --> 01:44:00,760
So what are we gonna do, Jack?

1307
01:44:01,840 --> 01:44:03,600
Jack?

1308
01:44:05,400 --> 01:44:08,320
I'll tell you exactly
what we're going to do.

1309
01:44:08,440 --> 01:44:11,080
You're going to do whatever
you have to do to find out...

1310
01:44:11,200 --> 01:44:13,960
which European company
he's been talking to.

1311
01:44:14,080 --> 01:44:16,920
Then I'm going to
clean myself up,

1312
01:44:17,000 --> 01:44:21,480
fly to Aspen and drink
eggnog with Bob Thomas.

1313
01:44:21,600 --> 01:44:25,360
His wife and kids will be playing
in the background in the snow...

1314
01:44:25,480 --> 01:44:28,240
while I convince him
that the European company...

1315
01:44:28,360 --> 01:44:30,200
is the devil...

1316
01:44:30,320 --> 01:44:33,720
and Global is the answer
to his prayers.

1317
01:44:33,840 --> 01:44:37,320
Then I'm gonna spend
four hours skiing... alone.

1318
01:44:38,560 --> 01:44:42,920
Completely and utterly alone.

1319
01:44:44,560 --> 01:44:48,040
I'm going to do that
because that is my life,

1320
01:44:48,160 --> 01:44:50,000
that's what's real...

1321
01:44:50,080 --> 01:44:52,680
and there's nothing
I can do to change that.

1322
01:45:09,840 --> 01:45:11,760
For Manhattan.

1323
01:45:11,880 --> 01:45:13,720
Kate Reynolds.

1324
01:45:18,360 --> 01:45:20,200
I need an address too.

1325
01:45:44,120 --> 01:45:46,840
It's very fragile, so I want you
to be very careful with it, okay?

1326
01:45:46,920 --> 01:45:49,240
It's valuable.
It's over 300 years old.

1327
01:45:49,360 --> 01:45:51,800
You'll probably need a few
guys to carry it. All right.

1328
01:45:51,920 --> 01:45:55,680
The painting is also very,
very old, so take extra care.

1329
01:45:55,760 --> 01:45:58,560
It means a lot to Kate, okay?
I appreciate it.

1330
01:45:59,920 --> 01:46:01,840
Yeah? What?

1331
01:46:01,960 --> 01:46:04,800
Are you from the moving
company? I'm Jack Campbell.

1332
01:46:04,920 --> 01:46:07,240
I'm an old... friend of Kate's.

1333
01:46:08,560 --> 01:46:10,400
Kate, some guy is here.

1334
01:46:10,480 --> 01:46:14,640
Did you call the airline like I asked
you to do? It's like two hours...

1335
01:46:14,720 --> 01:46:17,360
- Jack.
- Kate.

1336
01:46:17,520 --> 01:46:19,880
God, it's been a long time.
You look...

1337
01:46:19,960 --> 01:46:22,640
- You look great.
- Thanks.

1338
01:46:24,200 --> 01:46:26,880
I... Come on in.
Come on in.

1339
01:46:26,960 --> 01:46:30,240
I'm just doing some... Lori,
do you know where those boxes...

1340
01:46:31,960 --> 01:46:33,880
I'm sorry.

1341
01:46:34,080 --> 01:46:36,240
No, no, no! You know what... Jack.

1342
01:46:36,360 --> 01:46:38,520
Don't... Please.
I don't even care.

1343
01:46:38,600 --> 01:46:41,040
Oh, great. Thank you.

1344
01:46:42,280 --> 01:46:45,160
- What's going on?
- I'm moving to Paris.

1345
01:46:45,240 --> 01:46:48,400
Hey, Lori, have you seen that
box? It says "Jack" on it.

1346
01:46:48,480 --> 01:46:51,200
I put it with the rest
of the Salvation Army stuff.

1347
01:46:51,280 --> 01:46:53,400
Do you want me to look for the
box or call the airline, Kate?

1348
01:46:53,480 --> 01:46:56,320
Hey, kind of under
a little pressure here.

1349
01:46:56,440 --> 01:46:58,840
Hey, kind of giving up Christmas
day for my ex-boss here.

1350
01:46:58,960 --> 01:47:03,240
Hey, didn't mind offering to help when
she was opening the Prada bag I gave her.

1351
01:47:03,400 --> 01:47:06,720
- Maybe it's by the wardrobe boxes.
- Thank you.

1352
01:47:08,120 --> 01:47:11,120
- So you're moving.
- Yeah, to Paris.

1353
01:47:11,240 --> 01:47:14,520
My firm has an office there.
I'm gonna be heading it up.

1354
01:47:14,600 --> 01:47:17,440
Paris. Paris, France?

1355
01:47:17,520 --> 01:47:20,000
That's the one.

1356
01:47:20,120 --> 01:47:23,280
So you're... you're not
at a nonprofit firm?

1357
01:47:23,360 --> 01:47:25,720
God, no, not with
what they pay me.

1358
01:47:25,840 --> 01:47:28,080
Are you married?

1359
01:47:28,160 --> 01:47:31,560
No, I never got married,
Jack. You?

1360
01:47:31,640 --> 01:47:34,360
Not exactly.

1361
01:47:34,480 --> 01:47:36,680
Look, could we take a minute here,

1362
01:47:36,800 --> 01:47:38,840
maybe go get a cup of coffee
or something?

1363
01:47:38,960 --> 01:47:42,240
- I'll go for a cup of coffee.
- Yes. I found it.

1364
01:47:42,320 --> 01:47:44,800
Congratulations. Your
earlier flight was canceled,

1365
01:47:44,880 --> 01:47:47,160
but I got you out of
Kennedy on United at 7:00.

1366
01:47:47,240 --> 01:47:49,720
- Excellent.
- Am I good or what?

1367
01:47:49,800 --> 01:47:51,680
Yes, you're brilliant.

1368
01:47:51,760 --> 01:47:53,600
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1369
01:47:53,680 --> 01:47:57,160
Here you go. It's just
some old stuff of yours.

1370
01:47:57,240 --> 01:48:00,520
Do you ever think
about us, Kate?

1371
01:48:00,600 --> 01:48:02,440
About what might have happened?

1372
01:48:07,960 --> 01:48:09,800
Jack, I'll tell you what.

1373
01:48:09,920 --> 01:48:13,960
If you're ever in Paris, look me up and
we'll go have that cup of coffee, okay?

1374
01:48:14,040 --> 01:48:17,160
Or cafe. Or cafe au lait.
Oh, wait. No, no, no, no!

1375
01:48:17,240 --> 01:48:21,000
Don't close that up. I will
never find this box again.

1376
01:48:21,080 --> 01:48:24,000
Well, I marked it. Just
be more specific next time.

1377
01:48:27,720 --> 01:48:31,040
We'll leave it open then. I was
just trying to close it up.

1378
01:48:37,680 --> 01:48:39,520
Make a right here.

1379
01:48:39,600 --> 01:48:42,000
Sir, you're gonna be late
for your flight.

1380
01:48:42,120 --> 01:48:45,000
We're not going to the airport.

1381
01:50:08,640 --> 01:50:10,680
You can't leave this here.

1382
01:50:10,760 --> 01:50:12,640
You can't park here!

1383
01:50:35,920 --> 01:50:38,680
Kate! You can't go.

1384
01:50:38,800 --> 01:50:41,560
- Don't get on that plane.
- Jack?

1385
01:50:41,680 --> 01:50:44,320
Please, let's just go have a cup of
coffee. That's all I'm asking for.

1386
01:50:44,440 --> 01:50:47,640
I'm sure there's another
flight to Paris tonight.

1387
01:50:47,760 --> 01:50:51,440
Jack.
What are you doing here?

1388
01:50:55,440 --> 01:50:57,400
Do you need closure?

1389
01:50:57,480 --> 01:51:00,360
Because if you do, after
all these years, you got it.

1390
01:51:00,480 --> 01:51:03,200
I'm okay. I'm fine.

1391
01:51:04,800 --> 01:51:08,120
I... I was heartbroken, Jack,

1392
01:51:08,200 --> 01:51:11,520
but I got over it,
I moved on, and...

1393
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:15,960
you should move on too.

1394
01:51:16,040 --> 01:51:18,520
Okay? I'm sorry.

1395
01:51:18,680 --> 01:51:22,040
I just can't...
I've gotta go.

1396
01:51:22,240 --> 01:51:25,320
I-I... I'm sorry, Jack.
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

1397
01:51:30,160 --> 01:51:32,480
Can I just...
I'm sorry. I was here.

1398
01:51:44,120 --> 01:51:46,840
We have a house in Jersey!

1399
01:51:48,240 --> 01:51:50,520
We have two kids.

1400
01:51:50,640 --> 01:51:52,800
Annie and Josh.

1401
01:51:52,920 --> 01:51:56,520
Annie's not much of a violin
player, but she tries real hard.

1402
01:51:56,640 --> 01:52:01,680
She's a little precocious, but that's
only because she says what's on her mind.

1403
01:52:01,800 --> 01:52:04,800
And when she smiles...

1404
01:52:06,840 --> 01:52:08,680
And Josh,

1405
01:52:08,760 --> 01:52:10,920
he has your eyes.

1406
01:52:11,080 --> 01:52:14,440
He doesn't say much,
but we know he's smart.

1407
01:52:14,520 --> 01:52:16,640
He's always got his eyes open.

1408
01:52:16,760 --> 01:52:19,040
You know,
he's always watching us.

1409
01:52:19,160 --> 01:52:22,840
Sometimes you can look at him
and you just know...

1410
01:52:22,960 --> 01:52:25,440
he's learning something new.

1411
01:52:25,640 --> 01:52:27,960
It's like witnessing a miracle.

1412
01:52:28,040 --> 01:52:31,680
The house is a mess,
but it's ours.

1413
01:52:31,800 --> 01:52:36,160
After 120 more payments,
it's going to be ours.

1414
01:52:36,280 --> 01:52:39,920
And you,
you're a nonprofit lawyer.

1415
01:52:40,000 --> 01:52:43,800
That's right.
You're completely nonprofit.

1416
01:52:43,920 --> 01:52:46,360
But that doesn't seem
to bother you.

1417
01:52:48,720 --> 01:52:51,400
And we're in love.

1418
01:52:51,480 --> 01:52:54,880
After 13 years of marriage,
we're still unbelievably in love.

1419
01:52:56,440 --> 01:53:00,000
You won't even let me touch you
till I've said it.

1420
01:53:00,120 --> 01:53:01,920
I sing to you.

1421
01:53:02,000 --> 01:53:06,400
Not all the time, but
definitely on special occasions.

1422
01:53:06,480 --> 01:53:10,920
And we've... we've dealt with our share
of surprises and made a lot of sacrifices,

1423
01:53:11,000 --> 01:53:13,760
but we stayed together.

1424
01:53:13,840 --> 01:53:15,680
You see,

1425
01:53:16,880 --> 01:53:20,040
you're a better person
than I am,

1426
01:53:20,120 --> 01:53:24,680
and it made me a better
person to be around you.

1427
01:53:24,760 --> 01:53:27,240
I don't know. Maybe it
was all just a dream.

1428
01:53:27,360 --> 01:53:29,880
Maybe I went to bed one
lonely night in December,

1429
01:53:30,000 --> 01:53:32,440
and I imagined it all, but...

1430
01:53:32,600 --> 01:53:35,480
I swear, nothing's ever
felt more real.

